		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=108599">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Wizard of the Shadows" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Wizard+of+the+Shadows">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Wizard of the Shadows" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2076399&TN=Bard+Armor&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2076476&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">The difference between 103 CHA and 109 CHA will not likely be very noticeable.  If the new armor is a big upgrade in AC, other stats or resists I don't see a big problem using it.</P><P>As far as whether your Bard needs CHA.....Besides the obvious need to have it for buying and selling with merchants to get good prices, CHA is also very important for a Bard as you gain levels.</P><P>CHA is important for Charming and I believe Lulling and mezzing also.  I have also been told, and I believe it to be true, that CHA is needed to prevent skipped notes when you are trying to play a song.</P><P>For my Bard, I have been trying to increase STA, Dex, INT, and resists while keeping CHA high as well.  My 51 Bard has a CHA of about 150, but I would like it to much higher. By the way, I am also still wearing my newbie breastplate, but am looking to upgrade now that my gauntlets have more AC than it does...lol.  If it was for free, I probably would have upgraded to a Lambent BP. But, IIRC, it isn't all that great anyway.<BR>This just goes to show that a bard's armor isn't as important as the effectiveness of his songs for the group and soloing. If you plan to swarm-kite, you will need a higher CHA for charming.<BR>It is likely needed to effectively lull or mez the mobs in LDoN adventures as well.</P><P>Anyway, I am rambling.....You will need a high CHA, but a few points isn't going to kill you. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>Wizard of the 62nd Circle of Knowledge.<BR>Bard of the 51st silly song.<BR>Beasty of the 25th soloing level.<BR>Shadow Knight of the 10th level of Evil.<BR>12th level maker of viscous mana (Enchanter)</P><P>"There is always one more imbecile than you had planned for."<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
