		<hr size="1">if you get better AC out of it, then go for it.</P><P>my bard is at 130 or so CHA atm.  wish i had more INT (only in the upper 80s atm), but my HP, STA are nice.  </P><P>2 stats i need to work on are INT, and Dex.</P><P>CHA and Dex are the 2 main stats for missed notes on a bard, with CHA the prime stat.</P><P>normal jumps in performance are every 10 points.</P><P>so 70-80 would see a jump, 109-110 would see a jump, but 109-103 would not see a differance.</P><P>this is not FACT, this is just what i have observed over the years with most toons, and their prime stat.</P><P><hr><font style=font-size:8pt color=yellow>*Worlds worst speller*<BR><font color=yellow><BR>"For those who believe, then no proof is needed.  For those who are skeptics, then no proof will suffice."<font color=00FFFF><BR>"Pigs get fat, but Hogs get slaughtered and VI is a big HOG."<BR><font color=yellow> "So, reading some of my posts is sort of like having sex in your parents house???"  Dr. Zin</P><P></font><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
