		<hr size="1">Jobe, I didn't say that DEX had NO significance, I said it wasn't "as significant" as once was thought.</P><P>You know how tradeskills (with minor exception to smithing/fletching/jewelcraft) use either INT or WIS, whichever is higher.</P><P>It's the same with DEX/CHA, except that CHA is weighted even more so towards helping missed notes, etc.  Not to mention, if DEX helps only one thing (missed notes - I'm not counting proc's on weapons), then why not go towards CHA anyway since it's used for missed notes, charm, etc.  (ie more than one thing).</P><P>Remember, I used to think DEX was the be all, end all as well.  Hell, even had an item that lowered CHA but added DEX because I thought it was so important.</P><P>However, tests (and admission by SOE) show that CHA is very important towards bard fizzle rate (ie missed notes).</P><P>(everything above was learned via this forum, mainly)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
